  "market_context": "BTC weekly chart shows expansion lower, followed by consolidation and a sweep opposing the prior order flow, producing a candle 2 closure. Analyst skips the daily timeframe and drops directly to the 4-hour to look for a short continuation entry aligned with the weekly bearish bias.",
  "key_observation": "After a weekly candle 2 closure reversing a consolidation sweep, the 4-hour timeframe printed a sweep with a closure through the up-close candles, forming a protected swing high that could be sold with a defined stop and a 3R target toward lower swing lows.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the weekly context — expansion lower, consolidation, then a sweep opposing the prior order flow producing a candle 2 closure, signaling lower prices in the following candle.",
    "Step 2: Skip daily alignment and drop directly to the 4-hour timeframe while keeping weekly and daily reference charts visible.",
    "Step 3: On the 4-hour, observe price expanding away while respecting the lower half of the weekly wick, followed by a retracement/consolidation phase.",
    "Step 4: Wait for a 4-hour sweep of the local high followed by a closure through the up-close candles, forming an opposing candle / protected swing high.",
    "Step 5: Plan a short entry at the protected swing with stop above the swing high; note the wickless candle requires waiting for confirmation that price will not retrace into it.",
    "Step 6: Project targets — 3R to a nearer short-term objective, with extended target toward the lower swing lows (the level Daniel was targeting)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price moved quickly into the short-term objective and continued to hit the final take-profit level shown on the chart.",
  "lessons": "The fractal model can be applied across various timeframe combinations — weekly directly to 4-hour is valid for swing trading. Traders should choose the alignment that fits their style rather than forcing a fixed timeframe ladder.",
